The MS. is written in two columns, each containing 36 lines The rubrications and the capital letters are slightly more elaborate than the London Codex, and in consequence are, in my opinion, of a slightly later date, whilst the concluding words remove all possible suggestion of this having been the work of Thomas of Celano himself.
